[src:p-adic-analysis/hensel-s-lemma] There are two square roots of 17 in the 2-adic integers, differing by a sign, and although they are congruent mod 2 they are not congruent mod 4.
[src:p-adic-analysis/hensel-s-lemma] This is consistent with the general version of Hensel's lemma only giving us a unique 2-adic square root of 17 that is congruent to 1 mod 4 rather than mod 2.
